OL,3,CAstronaut urges world to preserve
OL,4,Coceans after seeing them from space
OL,6,FShe says: "It's absolutely
OL,7,Foverwhelming, you think you've
OL,8,Fprepared yourself for what it looks
OL,9,Flike and then just to have that
OL,10,Fextraordinary vantage point, it's a
OL,11,Freality check.
OL,13,F"When I looked out the window for the
OL,14,Ffirst time, the biggest part of it was
OL,15,Fthe ocean.
OL,17,F"Even though we know that water covers
OL,18,Fmost of our planet, I think in our
OL,19,Fdaily lives, unless you're standing by
OL,20,Fit, we don't necessarily acknowledge
OL,21,Fthat."
